					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9775712#post-4106495</guid>
				<title>Re: 3774 Question</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9775712/the-doctor-s-dilemma#post-4106495</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 02 Jan 2019 22:29:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Lt Flops</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1735419</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So, I'm basing this tale off of the Original Character Tournament continuity of 3774 (which is crosslinked in this article), where SCP-049 brings back Leslie from the dead and goes on an adventure with her to find Merle. Except during this,</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">spoiler</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Merle is shot and killed by a Foundation agent.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>I imagine that after this, Merle and Leslie's children were sent to a Foundation facility temporarily while they figure out what to do with them. This is indeed a stretch in logic, but I think it fits with the story I'm trying to tell.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
